Edition:
Quote: If New Zealand's littleness cramped that `elasticity of pride', there was always the capacious term `Australasia'. Little as it means on either side of the Tasman Sea today, it meant a great deal to the New Zealand poet or journalist of the nineteenth or early twentieth century. Melbourne and Sydney had bigger audiences; they had tastes of their own, and critics too, ... .  1. The term `Australasia' has been banned for many years - informally, as far as I know, but by common consent - in the New Zealand press.
